Xinhua News Agency Harbin, July 26: Black soil "planted" agricultural modernization
In summer, two aeroplanes sprayed chemicals from the second operation station of the fifth management area of Friendship Farm crossed the 10,000 mu high-yielding demonstration field, forming two white lines, green fields with black rice seedlings out of the "world's first field" several words particularly striking.
Kong Lingqiang, the station director, said such aircraft can spray more than 6,000 acres of cultivated land a day, about eight times more efficient than drones and hundreds of times more artificial.
This farm is located in Youyi County, Heilongjiang Province, China's largest grain-producing province. From the sound of rice cutting in the past to the sound of motors in the present, traditional Chinese farming and farming have transformed in this black soil belt.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in modern agricultural production at Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang introduced, on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural input, reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standard operation level of agricultural machinery field.
During this year's rice production, the farm expanded its operations with satellite navigation unmanned interpolation technology to 30,000 acres from 3,000 acres last year.
This technology makes seedling planting more uniform, maximizes the use of sunlight and farmland resources, and saves 16 yuan per acre in labor costs.
Farms try new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming China's largest agricultural machinery group from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the current total holdings of farm machinery 49,000 units (pieces), field comprehensive mechanization rate of 99.8.
Agricultural machinery operation to achieve GPS satellite navigation 100, dryland precision seeding 100, dryland high horsepower locomotive operation 100
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture, digital agriculture is the direction of agricultural modernization."
Friendship Farm director Liu Hualian said.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in technological progress.
In recent years, farmers in Heilongjiang have played a demonstration and leading role in modernizing large agricultural "aircraft carrier" and initially established a modern agricultural industry system dominated by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Youyi County, there is an agricultural machinery expo park covering 350,000 square meters.
There are more than 140 pieces of agricultural machinery imported and used by Heilongjiang farmers over the years.
These agricultural machinery and farms witnessed the development course of China's agricultural modernization.
