Upgraded Russian Armed Helicopter Ka-52M delivered for the first time at the end of the year
Moscow, July 25 (Xinhua) -- According to the plans of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the Ka-52M, an upgraded version of the Russian armed helicopter (hereinafter referred to as Wuzhi), will be completed in December this year for the first time.
According to the Russian news newspaper recently reported that Wuzhika-52M named "Super Alligator," its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year, currently the first batch of two of the upgraded version Wuzhi is undergoing modification and replacement of Russian "Progress" aerospace group Far East Helicopter Factory, its national testing and improvement work will be completed by October 2022.
According to Russian experts who understand the above upgrade work, "super alligator" "predecessor" - Wuzhika-52 was officially installed in November 2011, the model exposed some weaknesses in use, this upgrade is to "complement the short plate."
The report said that compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will partially use new protective materials that do not increase weight, its pilot cockpit will be reinforced with new equipment against missile attack, thereby increasing battlefield survival probability; equipped with more powerful generators to power more complex on-board electronic equipment; photoelectric system upgrade, capable of reconnaissance and identification of more distant battlefield targets; equipped with main attack armored combat vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications of the new light multi-purpose missile, with a range of 20 km, about 1 times more than the same missiles used by Russia in active military service; its defense weapons and communications equipment will be used to the maximum extent possible with the Mi-28NM helicopter gunships that can attack airborne targets, thus making related maintenance easy and economical.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapon targeting systems and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said it was worth noting that the Ka-52M would be equipped with communications equipment to communicate with drones, so as to get real-time information transmitted by nearby drones in the air, such as showing images taken by drones on the helicopter's cockpit screen.
It is planned that Ka-52M pilots will be able to directly control their matching UAVs, thus improving the pilot's knowledge of battlefield situations and guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Dmitry Krivoruchko said last December that the Russian Defense Ministry plans to purchase more than 110 WZK-52M by 2027.
