Recently, a Brazilian study showed that hydrochloroquine is ineffective in patients with mild coronavirus.
The study was published online in the New England Journal of Medicine.
Ba researchers divided 667 patients from 55 hospitals across the country into three groups to conduct a clinical trial that compared the effectiveness of treatment with hydroxychloroquine alone or in combination with other antibiotics azithromycin to determine whether it could help improve patients with mild and moderate coronavirus.
The results show that hydrochloroquine is not therapeutic but may have damaging side effects on organs.
